{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e6b35486-4898-4b3d-8fa1-c2f13272d3ba","content":"Here are the issues I found in `.template.config/template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing required field `identity`** — Every .NET template must have an `identity` field that uniquely identifies the template.\n\n2. **Invalid `datatype` value** — The symbol `myParam` uses `\"datatype\": \"invalid-type\"`, which is not a valid datatype. Valid values include: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, `string`.\n\n3. **Missing `sourceName`** — While not strictly required, most functional templates need a `sourceName` to enable name substitution during instantiation.\n\nTo fix, you'd want something like:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"author\": \"Test\",\n  \"classifications\": [\"Test\"],\n  \"identity\": \"Test.Template\",\n  \"name\": \"Test Template\",\n  \"shortName\": \"build\",\n  \"symbols\": {\n    \"myParam\": {\n      \"type\": \"parameter\",\n      \"datatype\": \"string\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3cbfe9f1-1875-4973-9e00-99f2fc0db84c","outputTokens":242,"requestId":"7829:115522:754998E:8190973:69F3FA96"},"id":"31beebf8-6109-491f-949c-0a675e96a946","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:58:04.270Z","parentId":"d46571ef-11ac-46ca-917c-e5e043921e68"}
